> Consider Ansible-Runner ports and adaptors to improve modularity through scalability.

## Portability

- [ ] Non-Debian package manager support — extend `auto-updates` role for `dnf` (Fedora), `pacman` (Arch), `zypper` (openSUSE), and `apk` (Alpine). *
- [ ] Non-systemd init support — service management (Podman quadlets, `loginctl enable-linger`) assumes systemd; add an init-system guard and document alternatives for OpenRC or runit targets.
- [ ] `SYSTEM_MOUNTS` in `storage_utils.py` has Pi-specific paths baked in (`/boot/firmware`) — consider an abstract class adaptor per platform/distro.
- [ ] Consider dropping the Homebrew role to be more platform-agnostic.

